1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:01,720
The Ateş Karahan I know,

2
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:04,960
would grab Mercan, his wife,
by the arm and bring her back.

3
00:00:05,360 --> 00:00:06,840
Mercan doesn't want that.

4
00:00:08,880 --> 00:00:12,000
She left without saying a
word, like she was escaping.

5
00:00:12,320 --> 00:00:14,720
If that's what she wants, she can have it.

6
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:17,720
What's the point of staying on the boat?

7
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:20,600
It's all because of
that murderer's daughter.

8
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:25,360
Even though they're getting divorced,
she is still his most precious thing.

9
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:28,160
Don't talk like that behind
her back, for god's sake.

10
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:30,080
What are you doing here?

11
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:32,000
I'll just see my mom and leave.

12
00:00:32,440 --> 00:00:36,160
I wish you hadn't come all the
way here and ruined our enjoyment.

13
00:00:36,760 --> 00:00:39,760
Mercan will stay here until
the day we get divorced.

14
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:43,400
I don't want a single problem
while she's in the mansion.

15
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:45,040
You won't upset Mercan,

16
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:48,080
you'll stay away from her.

17
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:51,480
Everyone pays for what they do, Dad.

18
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:52,760
You too.

19
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:55,400
I will never forgive you
for what I've been through.

20
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:59,720
If you don't feel comfortable, you
can come stay at us, with your mom.

21
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:03,240
I'll leave after you arrive.
You can spend time with Demet.

22
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:07,480
Why would she stay somewhere
else when she has a home?

23
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:09,760
It's an offer, not an insistence.

24
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:12,480
Your time is almost up, Ateş Karahan.

25
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:15,160
Everything and everyone has a due date.

26
00:01:15,960 --> 00:01:17,760
You’re such a shameless girl.

27
00:01:18,080 --> 00:01:19,720
Get out of our lives!

28
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:21,720
I don't care about your life.

29
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:26,240
These tickets are for 187 days
after the day we arrived here.

30
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:28,480
You didn't have any ticket back then.

31
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:31,760
If you have any dignity,
you wouldn't want this.

32
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,760
It hasn't been that long since I turned.

33
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,240
But I see,

34
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:36,760
nothing has changed.

35
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:38,080
In Italy,

36
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:42,480
There were no people constantly around me
belittling me and spreading negativity.”

37
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:44,280
Okay you turned, why did you lie?

38
00:01:44,440 --> 00:01:46,360
I saw the ring that fell out of your purse.

39
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:47,600
Why did you hide it?

40
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:49,200
I haven't wore it for a long time.

41
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:51,640
I didn't even know that it was in my purse.

42
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:53,000
Stop it!

43
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,600
Tell me you forgot about me.

44
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:56,120
Right now,

45
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:57,360
I'll go for good.

46
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,360
Tell me.

47
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:13,680
How would tell "I don't love you"?

48
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:16,960
Stop commanding me.

49
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:19,400
It's up yo me to tell that or not.

50
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:21,720
Tell me.

51
00:03:23,720 --> 00:03:25,360
Look me in the eye

52
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,200
and tell me, you forgot about me.

53
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:31,040
You didn't miss me.

54
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:34,720
And I'll go for good.

55
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:38,920
Like nothing has ever happened.

56
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,160
I can't when I love you so much.

57
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:43,720
I don't have to tell anything.

58
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:51,720
You can't.

59
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,560
Because you still love me.

60
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:58,760
Yet you stand here, lie to me.

61
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,360
It's you that's lying.

62
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:06,000
You loved me, yet you gave up on me.

63
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,200
I gave up?

64
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:11,000
You knew where I was.

65
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:14,000
But you didn't call,
you didn't come for me.

66
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,160
You were quiet for 100 days.

67
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:17,960
Is this love?

68
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,080
You left me.

69
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,800
Do you know what I'd been through here?

70
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:25,400
What about me?

71
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:27,320
Do you think it was easy?

72
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:30,960
I know it wasn't.

73
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,000
That day,

74
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:37,760
the last day we spent together.

75
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,520
I knew you were struggling

76
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:45,680
and still blaming yourself for the past.

77
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:32,920
I saw you were in pain.

78
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,000
That's why I didn't come.

79
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:41,880
For you

80
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,240
I gave up on you.

81
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,440
I left so that you wouldn't suffer.

82
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:53,000
You wouldn't remember the past.

83
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,120
Yeah?

84
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:56,480
Great.

85
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:58,680
You decided for me,

86
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:03,320
and put the divorce files, then left.

87
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:06,920
You also decided for me.

88
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:09,159
Why didn't you talk to me?

89
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,320
Why didn't you say anything?

90
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:11,840
You could've talked.

91
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:15,280
I stayed quiet thinking maybe
we could find a common path.

92
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,240
I waited.

93
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:19,200
You were so ready to leave.

94
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,640
Stop wagging your finger at me.

95
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:31,640
But you couldn't get rid of me, right?

96
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:35,080
Did you get rid of me?

97
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:42,040
You’re in a battle you can’t win.

98
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:46,040
I thought you liked losing to me.

99
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:57,680
You should've told me me to stay.

100
00:06:58,440 --> 00:07:00,880
You should have been the one
saying, ‘Leave the past behind.’

101
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,640
You didn’t give me a chance!

102
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:04,960
You ran away like a coward!

103
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,440
You can’t blame me

104
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:11,360
for not chasing after the
woman who wanted to divorce me!”

105
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:24,160
Now I understand even better
how right I was to leave!

106
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:27,640
You’re someone

107
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:29,360
who doesn’t even listen to what I say,

108
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,240
always does whatever you want,

109
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,040
and you’re completely full of yourself!

110
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:37,200
Yes, you did the best when you left.

111
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:43,600
You saved me from doing something
I would have regretted later.

112
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:04,560
If you don’t hesitate to throw it away…

113
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,840
then there’s no point in
me holding on to it either.

114
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:32,760
What's that champ

115
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:33,800
What's this anger?

116
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:34,880
What's the matter?

117
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,960
Mercan and I argued…

118
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:39,560
I went to talk to her,

119
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,760
but things suddenly got out of hand.

120
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:46,440
She says she left so I wouldn’t suffer,

121
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:49,720
and for the same reason, I
didn’t stop her from leaving.

122
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:54,040
Both of you gave up on each
other for each other’s sake

123
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:55,480
Is this it?

124
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,600
This isn't a secret.

125
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,320
What's this argue about?

126
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:02,600
You blame me, right?

127
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:04,880
I didn't say that.

128
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,520
I know you, Cemal.

129
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:11,040
Even if you say nothing.

130
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,920
I get it by your eyes.

131
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,640
Yeah, I blame you.

132
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,400
I told you before,

133
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,600
you should've taken the first step.

134
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:22,440
You should have gone to Italy
and told her how you feel.

135
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:25,440
You should have been the one to say
you wanted to leave the past behind.

136
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,640
When Mercan lied about
why she kept the ring

137
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,800
I got angry and pressed her about it.

138
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,720
When she threw the ring away,

139
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:46,600
of course I couldn’t
swallow my pride either

140
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,200
Love

141
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:53,680
really makes people do

142
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:56,400
the most ridiculous things

143
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,360
Logic on one side…

144
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,120
you on the other.

145
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:13,920
Is nothing wrong, right?

146
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:17,160
No…

147
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:18,880
I guess

148
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:20,760
I’m just a bit overwhelmed.

149
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:23,840
It feels like the family ties

150
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:25,960
between us

151
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:28,680
are breaking.

152
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,120
Me neither…

153
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:38,640
But I can’t feel any other way.

154
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:41,880
I still can’t forgive Aslı.

155
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,720
They were constantly
scheming behind my back.

156
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:48,680
I’m tired of being disappointed.

157
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:51,600
I can't trust them.

158
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:55,960
I mean,

159
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:57,520
Never mind this.

160
00:11:58,560 --> 00:11:59,560
Focus on Mecan.

161
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:02,080
Do you want to get divorced or not?

162
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:04,400
You'll get regret, it'll be too late.

163
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:05,560
I know you.

164
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:12,800
I don't want to.

165
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,560
Okay, what else?

166
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:17,640
No problem.

167
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:22,760
Well,

168
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:24,040
excuse me.

169
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,240
Mother.

170
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:04,960
Why aren't you in bed? You should rest.

171
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:09,640
Do you think resting will make me better?

172
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,480
Look,

173
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,720
I live like a stranger in my own house.

174
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,320
I’m afraid to even leave this room anymore.

175
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:22,480
Come on,

176
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:25,120
First, drink this herbal
tea without objecting.

177
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,920
My life has been turned upside down,

178
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,520
and you think herbal tea will help?

179
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:33,760
Look,

180
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:36,800
I’m not even treated like a
human being in my own house.

181
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:40,200
I’ve spent a lifetime in this room,

182
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:42,320
but even here I’m not comfortable anymore.

183
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:46,920
Mercan.

184
00:13:47,920 --> 00:13:49,400
Why are you getting divorced?

185
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:51,840
And you love each other.

186
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:56,120
And..

187
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:58,656
Wouldn’t it be better
if you didn’t get divorced

188
00:13:58,680 --> 00:14:01,480
and we didn’t have to keep wondering
what will happen to us like this?

189
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:02,840
Mother,

190
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,480
what are you saying?

191
00:14:06,040 --> 00:14:07,040
Daughter,

192
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:09,560
Ateş loves you

193
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:11,240
that boy is crazy about you.

194
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:14,240
If you don’t want it,
he would never divorce you.

195
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:15,936
If you won’t think about yourself,

196
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:17,080
then think about us.

197
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:19,640
How long are we going to
keep struggling like this?

198
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:21,560
I can’t believe you.

199
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:24,959
You have no idea what kind of pressure

200
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:27,080
I lived under because of
what happened in the past.

201
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:31,200
My daughter, why do you trouble
yourself so much over the past?

202
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,880
It’s called the past
for a reason. It passed.

203
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,400
How many times have I told you,

204
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:39,360
none of it was your fault.

205
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:42,800
Is Ateş so blind that he can’t see that?

206
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:48,160
Okay.

207
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,600
Okay, dear.

208
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,960
Alright, if you’re going to get divorced,

209
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:55,360
then demand a substantial alimony.

210
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:57,920
Let’s find a good lawyer.

211
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:00,120
You could even get compensation

212
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,560
This will never happen.

213
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,240
Daughter.

214
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:11,680
I'm telling this for your good.

215
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:14,840
Also for my good.

216
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:18,440
Don't look at me like that

217
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:21,000
You don’t have that much sense.

218
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:23,560
Sure.

219
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:26,040
You’ve never known what real hardship is.

220
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:27,840
But I do.

221
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:31,720
I know what it means not
to have a hot meal at home

222
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:35,120
the hardship of sleeping in the
cold, what it’s like to have no money.

223
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:37,680
You didn’t live through those things,

224
00:15:38,320 --> 00:15:39,840
you’re talking like this now.

225
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:42,160
I lived through it.

226
00:15:43,120 --> 00:15:44,760
And I never want to live like that again.

227
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:48,560
I can’t justify wrongdoing, Mom.

228
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:52,120
Even if I end up hungry or
homeless, that won’t change.

229
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:19,320
Mrs. Müzeyyen.

230
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:24,720
Put it like this.

231
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:30,760
How's marriage?

232
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,120
Good, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

233
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:35,760
It shows.

234
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:38,040
You neglect works.

235
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:40,320
Well,

236
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:42,480
You told me to not come for a couple days.

237
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:49,240
Get out.

238
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:52,640
Leave!

239
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:02,000
Did you talk Cemal, mom?

240
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:04,040
I didn't.

241
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:05,320
Don't worry.

242
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:06,920
He won't tell Ateş immediately.

243
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:08,640
Mom, why are you calm?

244
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:12,160
He might even be telling Ateş right now.

245
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:13,560
Enough.

246
00:17:14,320 --> 00:17:17,000
We’re going through all
this because of your stupidity.

247
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:19,840
And now you stand here to demand answers.

248
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:23,160
Cemal is not a man with a loose tongue.

249
00:17:24,440 --> 00:17:27,040
Don’t you know how
loyal this man is to Ateş?

250
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:29,920
Keeping quiet would be like betraying him.

251
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:33,280
Cemal doesn’t foul the plate he eats from.

252
00:17:33,920 --> 00:17:36,760
As much as he feels gratitude toward
Ateş, he feels the same toward me.

253
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:38,080
Mom, please.

254
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:40,320
Call him and talk.

255
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:43,560
I tell you to wait, so we'll wait.

256
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,120
Maybe you should stay away
from the house for a while

257
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:52,240
At least until the divorce is finalized.

258
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:55,520
I’ll talk to Cemal and sort everything out

259
00:17:56,120 --> 00:17:57,960
Are you kidding me?

260
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:02,160
Especially now, when Ateş
is about to get divorced…

261
00:18:03,080 --> 00:18:04,280
I’m not going anywhere.

262
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:38,760
I was lookin for a file,
didn't know you were here.

263
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:40,160
Mercan.

264
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,400
Plase stay.

265
00:18:59,720 --> 00:19:00,720
Why?

266
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:04,600
So I can stay and you can smash
things again like you did upstairs?

267
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:07,320
Mercan, have a little fairness.

268
00:19:07,960 --> 00:19:09,920
Whatever was said, it
was said on both sides.

269
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:12,560
It’s not like you were the only one hurt.

270
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:18,600
You started it though…

271
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,160
You pushed me too much.

272
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:22,960
Alright,

273
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:25,280
you’re right…

274
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:27,320
I’m sorry.

275
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:35,880
Look,

276
00:19:38,040 --> 00:19:39,120
you've been through.

277
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:43,400
Because of me.

278
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:47,320
You didn't deserve it.

279
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:50,440
Then…

280
00:19:57,080 --> 00:19:58,080
I understand you

281
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:00,760
And you understand me

282
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:05,680
I don’t want us to fight.

283
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:12,040
The last thing I’d
ever want is to hurt you.

284
00:20:20,280 --> 00:20:21,800
I don’t want to fight either.

285
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:25,040
We keep misunderstanding each other.

286
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:28,760
Anyway…

287
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:31,520
It doesn’t matter anymore

288
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:33,920
We’re about to get divorced…

289
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:38,120
If you stop reminding me of it…

290
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:47,240
You know the reasons.

291
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:49,840
Don’t be unfair to me.

292
00:20:51,080 --> 00:20:52,560
I know, okay.

293
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:57,880
Mercan… I can’t stand
you being cold toward me.

294
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:01,080
Even if we’re getting divorced

295
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:06,240
even if it’s going to
end, let it not end like this

296
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:08,360
Please. Okay?

297
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:14,960
Good…

298
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:18,000
Then let’s have dinner together tonight.

299
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:21,320
Without throwing plates
at each other, of course.

300
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,400
Okay,

301
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:25,080
I won’t throw anything

302
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:28,400
But you won’t provoke me either.

303
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:30,080
Deal…

304
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:32,520
Should we go out, or?

305
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:34,040
Here is fine.

306
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:36,600
Then we’re agreed.

307
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:07,680
What did you do? I was worried about you…

308
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:10,120
Were you able to solve
what’s been on your mind?

309
00:22:12,840 --> 00:22:13,840
No…

310
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:19,480
You look exhausted, Cemal.

311
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:24,280
Whatever it is, it’s not worth
wearing yourself down like this.

312
00:22:27,320 --> 00:22:30,280
I’m stuck in such a dilemma that…

313
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:32,800
Did you eat?

314
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:35,640
You didn’t eat at the office either.

315
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:38,320
Go eat something proper, Cemal.

316
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:39,960
Put your feet up, rest…

317
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:41,640
and let it be.

318
00:22:42,280 --> 00:22:44,080
If only it were that easy, Demet.

319
00:22:44,440 --> 00:22:45,440
If only..

320
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:48,400
Until I solve this, I can’t swallow a bite.

321
00:22:51,080 --> 00:22:52,400
Haven’t you left yet?

322
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:54,520
I’m leaving in a minute.

323
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:56,720
I had some things I needed to finish.

324
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:01,880
I have to go, Cemal… I’ll call you later.

325
00:23:05,160 --> 00:23:06,200
Who were you talking to?

326
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:08,680
A friend.

327
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:13,400
Why are you always here?

328
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:15,680
You don’t have any business
left at the company anymore.

329
00:23:15,960 --> 00:23:17,600
I’m not here out of curiosity.

330
00:23:18,160 --> 00:23:20,120
There are procedures that

331
00:23:22,320 --> 00:23:23,680
still need to be handled.

332
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:25,520
Is Mercan here?

333
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:27,840
She left.

334
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:33,040
When is the divorce?

335
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:37,600
In a few days. Why?
What are you going to do?

336
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:41,160
Demet.

337
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:42,840
I need your help.

338
00:23:45,840 --> 00:23:47,800
Make Mercan leave the mansion.

339
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:54,520
It’s not right for her to stay
there until the divorce anyway.

340
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:55,960
It’s not.

341
00:23:57,600 --> 00:23:59,120
She listens to you.

342
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:01,400
Convince her somehow.

343
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,000
Brother,

344
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:08,040
I’m not going to meddle in things
that aren’t my responsibility.

345
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:10,320
Mercan is a grown woman

346
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:12,360
She’ll do whatever she wants.

347
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:17,840
You should

348
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:20,280
focus on your own life now.

349
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:24,120
Because even if she divorces

350
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:26,480
Mercan won’t be with you.

351
00:24:31,080 --> 00:24:32,080
Don’t.

352
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:37,720
Don’t, Demet.

353
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:40,280
Don’t you ever talk like that again.

354
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:46,440
Mercan will eventually marry me…

355
00:24:54,120 --> 00:24:55,240
And if she won’t be mine…

356
00:24:57,640 --> 00:24:58,160
Yes…

357
00:24:58,440 --> 00:25:00,280
And if she won’t be, what will you do?

358
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:24,080
Hello.

359
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:26,680
Çiçek,

360
00:25:27,760 --> 00:25:29,720
when are we going shopping?

361
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:32,320
Shopping for what?

362
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:34,440
What do you mean?

363
00:25:35,920 --> 00:25:37,680
We’re coming to ask
for your hand, remember?

364
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:39,839
Malik, I have so much work to do…

365
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:42,320
And there are things waiting
for me at the mansion too.

366
00:25:42,520 --> 00:25:43,640
What work?

367
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:47,720
Skip it for one day. The
world won’t end, will it?

368
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:50,040
Not now.

369
00:25:50,960 --> 00:25:51,960
Look.

370
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:57,600
You’ve gotten so used to
carrying this job and your family

371
00:25:57,760 --> 00:26:00,160
that doing something for
yourself feels strange.

372
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:01,560
Let’s go

373
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:03,640
and buy you a beautiful dress.

374
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,399
I don’t know much, but
trays, Turkish delight

375
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:08,760
whatever we need, you tell me, I’ll buy it.

376
00:26:10,120 --> 00:26:11,960
Why spend that much?

377
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:13,880
You..
You’re not taking this

378
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:17,120
“asking for your hand” seriously.

379
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:19,560
What? Of course I am.

380
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:23,400
A person gets married once…

381
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,000
I mean, for me,

382
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:28,520
So I want to do everything
properly, the way it should be.

383
00:26:29,640 --> 00:26:30,760
But

384
00:26:31,560 --> 00:26:32,400
it’s all expenses.

385
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,320
If it costs money, then it costs money.

386
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:35,600
What?

387
00:26:35,720 --> 00:26:37,720
And I’m the one who wants it.

388
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:42,680
You… Wait a second…

389
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:44,800
Why don’t you want it?

390
00:26:45,120 --> 00:26:46,120
No..

391
00:26:46,760 --> 00:26:48,680
It's not that I don't want it.

392
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:52,000
You’ve already taken
everything on by yourself…

393
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:54,080
Look,

394
00:26:55,040 --> 00:26:56,840
I know you’re trying to be considerate.

395
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:59,600
You think about me.

396
00:27:00,800 --> 00:27:03,160
But sometimes too much of
it can be hurtful, Çiçek.

397
00:27:05,640 --> 00:27:06,640
Just so you know.

398
00:29:07,520 --> 00:29:08,640
You look beautiful.

399
00:29:10,320 --> 00:29:11,360
Thank you.

400
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:23,560
What are they doing?

401
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:36,960
It looks so beautiful.

402
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:41,680
Is this

403
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:44,840
a farewell dinner?

404
00:29:49,120 --> 00:29:50,120
I don’t know.

405
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:54,120
That’s not something
I can decide on my own.

406
00:29:59,560 --> 00:30:01,360
Wouldn’t it be better if we didn’t talk

407
00:30:02,720 --> 00:30:04,560
and just enjoyed the night?

408
00:30:13,640 --> 00:30:14,640
Thank you.

409
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:33,480
I asked Çiçek to have the
foods you love prepared.

410
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:37,880
I’ve missed Sister Binnaz’s cooking.

411
00:30:41,080 --> 00:30:43,120
So you’d choose this over Italian food.

412
00:30:44,840 --> 00:30:46,120
Without hesitation.

413
00:30:46,640 --> 00:30:48,440
For me, it’s always Turkish cuisine.

414
00:30:50,760 --> 00:30:52,480
And when it’s made by Sister Binnaz…

415
00:30:53,320 --> 00:30:54,440
even better.

416
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:04,920
This is great.

417
00:31:05,320 --> 00:31:06,320
Take some dolma.

418
00:31:14,320 --> 00:31:15,600
It's great, really.

419
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:22,480
I miss this.

420
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:00,720
It's her house.

421
00:32:01,560 --> 00:32:02,720
She comes when she wants,

422
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:05,040
She doesn't when she doesn't.

423
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:19,200
What are you doing here, this late?

424
00:32:20,080 --> 00:32:23,680
Mr. Ateş prepared a
romantic dinner for her.

425
00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:28,040
But I know how to ruin their night.

426
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,320
Enough!

427
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:33,480
I’m sick of these outbursts of yours!

428
00:32:33,520 --> 00:32:34,640
Let go of my arm.

429
00:32:35,400 --> 00:32:36,880
Get a grip!

430
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:38,720
You’ve completely lost it!

431
00:32:39,600 --> 00:32:41,280
Weren’t they getting divorced?!

432
00:32:41,720 --> 00:32:42,840
They are.

433
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:44,640
Then what is this?!

434
00:32:45,040 --> 00:32:46,400
Dinner with candles.

435
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:49,520
If Ateş wasn’t going to
divorce her, he would’ve said so.

436
00:32:51,120 --> 00:32:52,120
Look at that

437
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:55,840
she walked in and immediately
wrapped him around her finger again.

438
00:32:57,080 --> 00:33:01,240
And after everything, Mercan won’t
give up on divorcing him anyway.

439
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:05,160
Now stop causing trouble
for no reason and come inside.

440
00:33:40,520 --> 00:33:41,840
What are you trying to do?

441
00:33:43,360 --> 00:33:44,360
I’m trying to eat.

442
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:49,440
You know that’s not what I mean.

443
00:33:54,880 --> 00:33:56,120
How about you relax a little?

444
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:05,320
Why did you never call me?

445
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:13,560
As if you called me.

446
00:34:16,600 --> 00:34:17,640
A hundred days, Mercan…

447
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:21,520
For a hundred days, you didn’t call once.

448
00:34:23,120 --> 00:34:24,440
If you had called, Ateş.

449
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:26,880
You were the one who left.

450
00:34:29,600 --> 00:34:30,960
You know why I left.

451
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:34,120
I couldn’t call.

452
00:34:35,680 --> 00:34:37,160
I wanted to, so many times.

453
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:39,960
Every time…

454
00:34:41,640 --> 00:34:43,160
You were afraid I’d blame you.

455
00:34:45,040 --> 00:34:46,200
When you learned the truth,

456
00:34:46,640 --> 00:34:48,640
you said: “We can’t
have a future together."

457
00:34:54,640 --> 00:34:56,480
You decided to leave too.

458
00:34:57,400 --> 00:34:58,400
Don’t forget that.

459
00:35:04,200 --> 00:35:05,200
Mercan…

460
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:10,400
I never blamed you

461
00:35:12,720 --> 00:35:13,720
Yes,

462
00:35:14,640 --> 00:35:16,520
at first I was so angry at your father

463
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:18,480
I turned it on you too. I was unfair.

464
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:25,240
Deep down, I always knew you were innocent.

465
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:31,440
That doesn’t change what happened.

466
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:38,520
If only

467
00:35:41,080 --> 00:35:43,800
this marriage had started
under different circumstances…

468
00:35:51,640 --> 00:35:52,640
If only…

469
00:36:14,120 --> 00:36:15,280
Would you like to dance?

470
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:30,120
What happens now, Mercan?

471
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:37,000
I don’t know.

472
00:38:37,960 --> 00:38:39,040
I haven’t thought about it.

473
00:38:40,960 --> 00:38:42,800
What are you thinking of doing?

474
00:38:45,240 --> 00:38:46,360
I don’t have a plan.

475
00:38:49,480 --> 00:38:50,960
You didn’t plan to go somewhere?

476
00:38:52,640 --> 00:38:53,640
No.

477
00:38:54,320 --> 00:38:55,320
I

478
00:38:56,680 --> 00:38:58,000
Thought you were going to leave.

479
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:00,680
That you had plans.

480
00:39:03,040 --> 00:39:04,240
I have no plans.

481
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:06,720
I didn’t think.

482
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:11,480
I’ve been living without you for months…

483
00:39:14,320 --> 00:39:16,320
And right now… I only want to live you.

484
00:39:54,160 --> 00:39:55,720
Why won’t that girl leave our lives?

485
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:58,160
When she wasn’t here,
everything was so fine!

486
00:39:59,760 --> 00:40:01,280
Everything wasn’t fine.

487
00:40:03,600 --> 00:40:05,360
Ateş wouldn’t even talk to you.

488
00:40:06,440 --> 00:40:08,840
Are you my mother or my enemy?

489
00:40:10,800 --> 00:40:12,040
Why are you always stopping me?

490
00:40:12,720 --> 00:40:14,800
Why won’t you let me be with Ateş?

491
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:22,120
For years I’ve tried to make
you give up this obsession.

492
00:40:24,080 --> 00:40:25,520
I want you to see the truth.

493
00:40:26,240 --> 00:40:28,760
Because I know Ateş
looks at you like a sister.

494
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:29,800
Don’t.

495
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:31,400
Don't mom.

496
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:32,840
I don’t want to hear it.

497
00:40:34,320 --> 00:40:36,120
Tomorrow morning you’re
leaving this mansion.

498
00:40:37,800 --> 00:40:40,160
When our business here is
done, I’ll come to you as well.

499
00:40:40,960 --> 00:40:42,160
I’m not going anywhere!

500
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:53,120
Why is the door locked?

501
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:55,440
Right, you're not going anywhere.

502
00:40:58,000 --> 00:41:01,120
With this anger of yours, I’m
not leaving you on your own.

503
00:41:03,240 --> 00:41:04,920
Tonight you’re staying here with me.

504
00:41:05,440 --> 00:41:07,320
Don’t be ridiculous. Give me the key.

505
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:11,440
Mom!

506
00:41:11,920 --> 00:41:13,880
I’ll scream and wake the whole house!

507
00:41:15,480 --> 00:41:16,920
Scream.

508
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:20,400
And then you can explain to Ateş and
everyone else why you’re screaming.

509
00:41:21,400 --> 00:41:22,400
Mom!

510
00:41:45,760 --> 00:41:47,600
What happened to you, Aslı?

511
00:41:51,960 --> 00:41:54,200
Or were you always like this
and I just couldn’t see it?

512
00:42:07,600 --> 00:42:08,680
Good evening.

513
00:42:10,280 --> 00:42:11,800
Good evening, Malik. Come in.

514
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:17,680
You wanted to see me.

515
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:19,200
Yes.

516
00:42:21,680 --> 00:42:23,440
Sorry it’s late,

517
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:26,320
but you said “no matter what
time it is, have him come,”

518
00:42:26,360 --> 00:42:26,920
so…

519
00:42:26,960 --> 00:42:28,120
Don’t mention it.

520
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:29,360
No need.

521
00:42:29,560 --> 00:42:30,560
That's okay.

522
00:42:31,560 --> 00:42:33,720
You’ve got a lot on your plate these days.

523
00:42:35,040 --> 00:42:36,040
Here.

524
00:42:37,760 --> 00:42:38,760
This is yours.

525
00:42:40,200 --> 00:42:41,440
What is this?

526
00:42:41,840 --> 00:42:42,840
Mr. Ateş

527
00:42:43,040 --> 00:42:44,360
wanted to give you a small bonus.

528
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:47,536
He said, not to worry about the wedding

529
00:42:47,560 --> 00:42:49,080
we’ll do it in the best way.”

530
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:52,120
Thanks. There was no need.

531
00:42:52,160 --> 00:42:55,720
Having Mr. Ateş and Mrs.
Mercan with us is enough

532
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:58,320
Of course they’ll be with you.

533
00:42:59,080 --> 00:43:01,136
But if you accept it, you’ll
make Mr. Ateş very happy.

534
00:43:01,160 --> 00:43:02,160
Just so you know.

535
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:04,800
Thanks a lot.

536
00:43:07,120 --> 00:43:09,280
They’re both very happy for you.

537
00:43:10,480 --> 00:43:12,440
Whatever you need,

538
00:43:12,760 --> 00:43:14,480
we’re here, okay?

539
00:43:15,440 --> 00:43:17,040
Thank you…

540
00:43:18,440 --> 00:43:19,440
Here, Malik.

541
00:43:23,040 --> 00:43:24,160
Thanks, Mr. Cemal.

542
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:27,680
If you excuse me.

543
00:43:27,800 --> 00:43:28,800
Absolutely.

544
00:43:29,320 --> 00:43:31,040
Good night.

545
00:43:59,800 --> 00:44:02,360
I haven’t had such a good time in so long…

546
00:44:03,040 --> 00:44:04,040
Thank you.

547
00:44:05,440 --> 00:44:06,520
Thank you.

548
00:44:06,720 --> 00:44:07,720
Mrs. Mercan.

549
00:44:18,840 --> 00:44:19,840
Look

550
00:44:20,440 --> 00:44:21,480
A shooting star…

551
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:23,440
right there.

552
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:24,920
Let’s make a wish.

553
00:44:35,440 --> 00:44:37,040
I don't want to leave you.

554
00:45:09,280 --> 00:45:10,280
What did you wish for?

555
00:45:13,280 --> 00:45:14,400
I won’t tell you…

556
00:45:20,040 --> 00:45:21,960
Or it won’t come true.

557
00:45:24,240 --> 00:45:26,040
Do you believe it will?

558
00:45:32,360 --> 00:45:33,600
Maybe it will.

559
00:45:41,760 --> 00:45:43,480
Um… I should go change.

560
00:45:59,040 --> 00:46:00,040
Let’s stay like this.

561
00:46:06,720 --> 00:46:07,720
Um…

562
00:46:12,760 --> 00:46:13,920
Don’t leave right away.

563
00:46:15,240 --> 00:46:17,320
When I come out, we’ll talk a little.

564
00:46:19,920 --> 00:46:20,920
I’ll be here.

565
00:46:28,080 --> 00:46:29,320
As long as you want…

566
00:47:14,720 --> 00:47:16,480
My only wish is you.

567
00:47:16,840 --> 00:47:18,200
My pearl, Mercan.

568
00:47:30,160 --> 00:47:31,680
What happens now, Mercan?

569
00:47:37,480 --> 00:47:38,480
I don’t know…

570
00:47:39,480 --> 00:47:40,760
I didn't think.

571
00:47:42,560 --> 00:47:44,160
Did you think what you're going to do?

572
00:47:46,880 --> 00:47:47,880
I have no plan.

573
00:47:50,960 --> 00:47:52,400
You didn’t plan to go somewhere?

574
00:47:54,240 --> 00:47:55,240
No.

575
00:47:56,280 --> 00:47:57,280
I..

576
00:47:58,640 --> 00:48:00,120
Thought you were going to leave.

577
00:48:01,480 --> 00:48:02,720
That you had plans.

578
00:48:04,040 --> 00:48:05,440
I have no plans.

579
00:48:06,840 --> 00:48:07,840
I didn't think.

580
00:48:07,880 --> 00:48:09,880
I live without you for months.

581
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:15,840
Right now… I only want to live you.

582
00:48:52,200 --> 00:48:53,200
Ateş?

583
00:49:01,200 --> 00:49:03,200
You looked like you were
having a beautiful dream.

584
00:49:18,400 --> 00:49:19,400
Yes…

585
00:49:20,680 --> 00:49:22,640
A very beautiful dream.

586
00:49:23,560 --> 00:49:24,560
Really?

587
00:49:26,640 --> 00:49:28,000
Tell me.

588
00:50:05,200 --> 00:50:06,720
A little bit more.

589
00:50:06,760 --> 00:50:07,760
Hmm…

590
00:50:08,680 --> 00:50:10,520
Not bad at all.

591
00:50:26,720 --> 00:50:27,880
Not bad at all.

592
00:50:33,680 --> 00:50:34,680
Good morning.

593
00:50:36,080 --> 00:50:37,080
Good morning.

594
00:50:37,960 --> 00:50:40,640
I made your favorite dessert for you.

595
00:50:40,760 --> 00:50:42,200
So we can eat something sweet

596
00:50:42,760 --> 00:50:44,200
and speak sweetly.

597
00:50:48,880 --> 00:50:51,120
Does everything get better
just because you eat dessert?

598
00:50:51,920 --> 00:50:53,600
Maybe it does?

599
00:50:55,320 --> 00:50:57,720
Are you trying to make it up to me?

600
00:50:58,320 --> 00:51:00,160
I didn’t mean to hurt you, Malik.

601
00:51:00,840 --> 00:51:04,000
I just don’t want you
spending money to make me happy.

602
00:51:04,320 --> 00:51:06,080
Let’s live within our means.

603
00:51:07,840 --> 00:51:08,840
Look, my love..

604
00:51:10,040 --> 00:51:12,160
Sometimes we live within our means…

605
00:51:12,760 --> 00:51:15,880
and sometimes we splurge a
little for our happy moments.

606
00:51:16,720 --> 00:51:18,600
Life isn’t one flat line.

607
00:51:19,160 --> 00:51:20,680
You’ll live everything you deserve

608
00:51:21,240 --> 00:51:23,320
as long as we can afford it.

609
00:51:24,320 --> 00:51:25,320
Okay?

610
00:51:25,360 --> 00:51:26,360
Alright.

611
00:51:27,040 --> 00:51:28,040
Taste it.

612
00:51:30,360 --> 00:51:31,360
Okay.

613
00:51:32,440 --> 00:51:35,560
Now let’s taste this
amazing-looking dessert.

614
00:51:50,400 --> 00:51:51,880
It's amazing.

615
00:51:52,160 --> 00:51:53,800
I'm proud of myself.

616
00:51:54,560 --> 00:51:56,840
Almost as good as my mom’s.

617
00:51:58,000 --> 00:51:59,120
Let me taste it.

618
00:51:59,160 --> 00:51:59,720
Let's see.

619
00:52:00,040 --> 00:52:01,040
Let's see.

620
00:52:04,920 --> 00:52:05,920
How is it?

621
00:52:08,240 --> 00:52:09,400
Amazing.

622
00:52:10,120 --> 00:52:11,640
Don’t let your mom hear this…

623
00:52:11,840 --> 00:52:15,440
but this is one level above hers.

624
00:52:17,320 --> 00:52:18,320
Then..

625
00:52:26,520 --> 00:52:28,880
I'll make you so many desserts.

626
00:52:29,080 --> 00:52:30,160
Here.

627
00:52:30,240 --> 00:52:31,480
This is nothing.

628
00:52:31,520 --> 00:52:32,520
So many.

629
00:52:38,800 --> 00:52:39,800
Take this.

630
00:53:18,440 --> 00:53:20,120
I love you so much.

631
00:53:26,560 --> 00:53:28,360
For me, life is you.

632
00:53:31,560 --> 00:53:34,600
Whatever you do, wherever you go

633
00:53:36,240 --> 00:53:38,080
you’ll never be able
to tear me away from you.

634
00:53:42,120 --> 00:53:43,560
Because you’re always inside me.

635
00:55:15,920 --> 00:55:17,840
You can’t compete with my love.

636
00:55:29,800 --> 00:55:31,200
Then why am I getting divorced?

637
00:55:39,760 --> 00:55:40,760
Good morning.

638
00:55:42,600 --> 00:55:43,680
Good morning, my girl.

639
00:55:44,480 --> 00:55:45,880
Can I have the key?

640
00:55:47,040 --> 00:55:48,160
You were right.

641
00:55:48,560 --> 00:55:49,800
I was very angry last night.

642
00:55:51,200 --> 00:55:53,320
To be honest, it was
good that I stayed here.

643
00:55:54,280 --> 00:55:58,320
If I’d done something else recklessly,
Ateş would never have forgiven me.

644
00:56:11,120 --> 00:56:12,560
Pack your suitcase.

645
00:56:12,600 --> 00:56:14,160
We’re leaving without having breakfast.

646
00:56:14,760 --> 00:56:15,960
I’m not going anywhere.

647
00:56:16,800 --> 00:56:17,680
Don’t start again…

648
00:56:17,681 --> 00:56:18,720
Be smart for once!

649
00:56:19,360 --> 00:56:20,720
And you’re going to be a lawyer!

650
00:56:21,120 --> 00:56:23,920
I told you a hundred times,
we can’t fall out with Ateş.

651
00:56:24,640 --> 00:56:27,280
And I’m telling you I’m not
going to do something stupid!

652
00:56:28,880 --> 00:56:30,480
You can scream as much as you want

653
00:56:30,600 --> 00:56:32,280
today you’re leaving this mansion

654
00:56:33,080 --> 00:56:35,040
When the divorce
happens, you can come back.

655
00:57:10,000 --> 00:57:11,000
Move.

656
00:57:11,080 --> 00:57:12,160
Don’t mess with me.

657
00:57:12,560 --> 00:57:14,680
If anyone’s leaving, it’s you!

658
00:57:15,240 --> 00:57:17,240
I’ll leave whenever I feel like it.

659
00:57:19,040 --> 00:57:21,520
You really love staying
where you’re not wanted.

660
00:57:23,440 --> 00:57:25,200
You’re leaving in a few days anyway.

661
00:57:25,720 --> 00:57:26,880
Why are you pushing it?

662
00:57:27,760 --> 00:57:29,280
Ateş doesn’t want you.

663
00:57:29,720 --> 00:57:31,240
He was perfectly happy without you.

664
00:57:31,840 --> 00:57:33,880
He’s counting the days
until he’s rid of you.

665
00:57:34,480 --> 00:57:35,480
Is that so?

666
00:57:36,520 --> 00:57:37,600
Let’s say it is

667
00:57:39,200 --> 00:57:41,800
why do you care about
our marriage this much?

668
00:57:42,640 --> 00:57:43,640
What is your problem?

669
00:57:49,200 --> 00:57:51,680
And you lied about Ateş’s future plans too…

670
00:57:58,160 --> 00:57:59,720
We love each other!

671
00:58:00,400 --> 00:58:02,320
You should accept that fact already.

672
00:58:04,160 --> 00:58:05,400
He’s going to divorce you.

673
00:58:05,760 --> 00:58:06,880
Get out.

674
00:58:14,200 --> 00:58:15,760
Maybe we won’t divorce after all, Aslı.

675
00:58:34,120 --> 00:58:35,680
Maybe we won’t divorce after all, Aslı.

676
00:58:41,640 --> 00:58:42,640
Cemal

677
00:58:43,240 --> 00:58:44,760
What did you want to talk to me about?

678
00:58:45,480 --> 00:58:47,960
Uh… first… tell me how last night went.

679
00:58:48,440 --> 00:58:51,040
I can tell you what I came to say later.

680
00:58:52,600 --> 00:58:53,720
It was beautiful…

681
00:58:58,640 --> 00:59:00,120
After a peaceful dinner,

682
00:59:00,720 --> 00:59:02,560
we talked until late…

683
00:59:10,480 --> 00:59:12,360
I don’t want to leave Mercan, Cemal.

684
00:59:14,520 --> 00:59:16,120
Last night, I understood that even more.

685
00:59:20,200 --> 00:59:21,200
And Mercan?

686
00:59:22,120 --> 00:59:23,120
What does she think?

687
00:59:25,320 --> 00:59:26,640
She doesn’t want to leave either.

688
00:59:29,240 --> 00:59:30,280
I love my wife.

689
00:59:37,040 --> 00:59:38,600
A man experiences a love like this

690
00:59:39,040 --> 00:59:40,880
once in his life, brother.

691
00:59:48,320 --> 00:59:49,560
I don’t want to lose it.

692
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:01,760
I’m not interrupting, am I, boys?

693
01:00:02,760 --> 01:00:03,760
No.

694
01:00:04,880 --> 01:00:06,120
Did you want to talk to me?

695
01:00:07,320 --> 01:00:09,880
No, I need to speak with Cemal

696
01:00:17,280 --> 01:00:17,800
Alright…

697
01:00:18,240 --> 01:00:19,600
I was leaving anyway.

698
01:00:20,240 --> 01:00:21,240
See you, Cemal.

699
01:00:21,600 --> 01:00:22,600
Okay.

700
01:00:28,040 --> 01:00:29,760
So… you still haven’t told Ateş.

701
01:00:31,400 --> 01:00:33,440
Looks like Aslı asked you for help.

702
01:00:34,280 --> 01:00:36,240
You have to stay silent, Cemal.

703
01:00:39,480 --> 01:00:41,800
Did you know about the
things she’s been doing?

704
01:00:43,160 --> 01:00:45,320
I didn’t. I found out later.

705
01:00:49,280 --> 01:00:51,840
If I had known, would I have
let her get herself into trouble?

706
01:00:52,600 --> 01:00:55,320
These aren’t things you hide.

707
01:00:55,840 --> 01:00:59,000
A healthy person doesn’t
do things like this.

708
01:00:59,880 --> 01:01:00,880
Enough, Cemal.

709
01:01:01,400 --> 01:01:03,440
In the end, Mercan didn’t die, did she?

710
01:01:03,760 --> 01:01:05,840
There’s no point in going to tell Ateş now.

711
01:01:05,880 --> 01:01:07,320
But she could have, Mother Müzeyyen.

712
01:01:09,160 --> 01:01:10,520
You call me “Mother Müzeyyen”

713
01:01:11,360 --> 01:01:12,840
because I’ve done a lot for you.

714
01:01:13,040 --> 01:01:15,040
For the sake of that
alone, you must keep quiet.

715
01:02:00,000 --> 01:02:01,600
This is your end, Mercan.

716
01:02:02,000 --> 01:02:02,640
Today,

717
01:02:02,880 --> 01:02:04,360
is your last day.

718
01:03:16,240 --> 01:03:17,240
You, again?

719
01:03:17,960 --> 01:03:20,280
What kind of person
are you? you never learn!

720
01:03:35,520 --> 01:03:37,040
So you love Ateş…

721
01:03:51,920 --> 01:03:53,720
and you don’t intend to divorce him.

722
01:03:54,440 --> 01:03:55,440
Aslı,

723
01:03:55,760 --> 01:03:56,760
Put the knife down.

724
01:03:57,080 --> 01:03:58,200
I warned you so many times,

725
01:04:01,480 --> 01:04:03,480
but you never listened!

726
01:04:10,880 --> 01:04:13,160
Aslı, please…

727
01:04:15,360 --> 01:04:16,520
Calm down. Put it down.

728
01:04:19,520 --> 01:04:21,120
Please… calm down.

729
01:04:23,440 --> 01:04:24,520
What?

730
01:04:24,680 --> 01:04:26,280
A minute ago you weren’t begging…

731
01:04:26,840 --> 01:04:27,840
This time

732
01:04:27,920 --> 01:04:29,880
you won’t get away from me.

733
01:04:29,920 --> 01:04:30,920
This time?

734
01:04:32,040 --> 01:04:32,600
Yes,

735
01:04:33,000 --> 01:04:34,000
this time.

736
01:04:35,960 --> 01:04:37,640
You’re like you have nine lives…

737
01:04:37,800 --> 01:04:39,439
but you’ve come to the end.

738
01:04:39,440 --> 01:04:40,560
What are you saying?

739
01:04:48,040 --> 01:04:49,040
You won't get away.

740
01:04:50,600 --> 01:04:53,240
You won't get away this
time! Did you hear me?

741
01:04:55,280 --> 01:04:56,600
I'll kill you!

742
01:04:57,640 --> 01:04:58,760
Get a grip!

743
01:05:13,000 --> 01:05:14,000
Let go off me!

744
01:05:20,520 --> 01:05:22,000
Have you lost your mind?

745
01:05:23,280 --> 01:05:25,000
You just wouldn’t die!

746
01:05:25,720 --> 01:05:27,120
I arranged everything.

747
01:05:27,400 --> 01:05:28,920
You just wouldn’t die!

748
01:05:29,560 --> 01:05:30,840
I shot you, it didn’t work…

749
01:05:31,360 --> 01:05:33,120
I kidnapped you, it didn’t work either!

750
01:05:33,560 --> 01:05:34,560
In that pool,

751
01:05:34,760 --> 01:05:36,520
you were supposed to drown!

752
01:05:37,000 --> 01:05:38,800
Every time you escaped from me.

753
01:05:39,520 --> 01:05:43,280
But this time you won’t!

754
01:05:44,880 --> 01:05:46,040
Help me!

755
01:05:57,360 --> 01:05:58,720
I shot you, it didn’t work…

756
01:05:59,000 --> 01:06:00,720
I kidnapped you, it didn’t work either!

757
01:06:01,160 --> 01:06:02,680
You just wouldn’t die!
